---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'About — The Second Design',
  description:
    'The Second Design is an education design studio led by Gautham and Aruna, focused on building real-world learning environments.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>

  <!-- Hero ************************************* -->
  <section class="py-24 text-center bg-white dark:bg-slate-950">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
        About The Second Design
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        We are an education design studio that cares deeply about how people learn in the real world —
        not just how they pass exams.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who we are ******************************* -->
  <section
    class="py-20 text-center border-y
           border-slate-200 bg-slate-50
           dark:bg-slate-950/70 dark:border-slate-800"
  >
    <div class="container max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-10 px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
        Who is behind The Second Design?
      </h2>

      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2 text-left">
        <!-- Gautham -->
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-4 border
                 bg-white border-slate-200 shadow-sm shadow-slate-200/80
                 dark:bg-slate-900/60 dark:border-slate-800/70 dark:shadow-black/25"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Gautham
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Educator, builder, and long-time experimenter in the Indian education ecosystem.
            Over the last decade, Gautham has worked across student startup incubators, ed-tech, and
            real-world skill building programs — always with one question in mind:
            <span class="italic">“What actually helps people move in the real world?”</span>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            At The Second Design, he focuses on program architecture, learner experience, and making sure
            every initiative is grounded in reality, not buzzwords.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Aruna -->
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-4 border
                 bg-white border-slate-200 shadow-sm shadow-slate-200/80
                 dark:bg-slate-900/60 dark:border-slate-800/70 dark:shadow-black/25"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Aruna
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Aruna brings the rigor of organised academia and research into our work.
            With a background that includes astrophysics research at Harvard, she has spent years
            thinking about how complex ideas can be taught clearly, honestly, and playfully.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            At The Second Design, she leads curriculum design, scaffolding of concepts, and the emotional
            safety of the learning space — so that students and participants can actually try, fail, and grow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we believe ************************** -->
  <section class="py-24 text-center bg-white dark:bg-slate-950">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-10 px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
        What we believe about learning
      </h2>

      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3 text-left">
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Agency over compliance
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Real learning shows up as initiative — the ability to start, ask, ship, and adapt.
            We design for agency first, not attendance or completion rates.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Systems over hacks
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Instead of one-off tips and tricks, we focus on mental models and systems that
            learners can reuse across domains and through different phases of life.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Feeling matters
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            People don’t just learn with their brains. Safety, identity, and emotion shape whether a
            program lands or bounces off. We design for that layer explicitly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we actually do ********************** -->
  <section
    class="py-20 text-center border-y
           border-slate-200 bg-slate-50
           dark:bg-slate-950/70 dark:border-slate-800"
  >
    <div class="container max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-10 px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
        What we actually do day to day
      </h2>

      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-base leading-relaxed">
        Most of our work falls into two buckets:
        <span class="font-semibold"> designing programs for others</span> and
        <span class="font-semibold"> running our own flagship program, Real World Ready.</span>
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2 text-left">
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-3 border
                 bg-white border-slate-200 shadow-sm shadow-slate-200/80
                 dark:bg-slate-900/60 dark:border-slate-800/70 dark:shadow-black/25"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Consulting & program design
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We partner with businesses, nonprofits, and colleges to design learning environments:
            academies, finishing-school style tracks, youth programs, and internal capability-building initiatives.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You bring the domain expertise. We help shape it into curriculum, experiences, and structures that
            people can actually move through.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-3 border
                 bg-white border-slate-200 shadow-sm shadow-slate-200/80
                 dark:bg-slate-900/60 dark:border-slate-800/70 dark:shadow-black/25"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
            Real World Ready
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Our own flagship program for students and young professionals, often run under co-branded names
            with partners like TinkerHub. It focuses on agency, system design for life, and navigating an uncertain future.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You can think of it as a parallel “real-world curriculum” that sits alongside formal education.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA ************************************** -->
  <section class="py-24 text-center bg-white dark:bg-slate-950">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">
        Want to design a serious learning experience?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-base leading-relaxed">
        If you’re thinking about a program for your students, community, or team, we’re happy to explore it with you.
        No pitch deck, no jargon — just an honest conversation about what you’re trying to make possible.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4 pt-4">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl
                 bg-slate-900 text-slate-50 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold
                 shadow-lg shadow-blue-500/30 hover:bg-slate-800
                 dark:bg-white dark:text-slate-900 dark:hover:bg-slate-100
                 transition"
        >
          Book an inquiry call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>